en:
Please provide details of whether you have implemented a health and safety management system for transport activities relevant to the services provided. If so, please provide evidence of process or procedure with the health and safety management system. The outline should contain details of the following minimum requirements: 

(i)           Risk assessments, risk management and monitoring; 
(ii)          Hazard and incident reporting; 
(iii)         Evidence of management commitment (including relevant policies, leadership reporting etc.);
(iv)         Internal health and safety investigation processes; 
(v)          Health and safety training, supervision and communication (including information and instruction);
(vi)         Health and safety performance monitoring; 
(vii)        Consultation processes (including with customers, subcontractors and third parties); and 
(viii)       Assurance, continuous improvement and change management processes.

Please provide an outline of the processes you have developed in order to comply with your obligations under the HVNL, including processes to manage the specific risks of;

(i) Speed compliance;
(ii) Fatigue management;
(iii) Mass, dimension and loading (including load restraint); 
(iv) Maintenance Management; and
(v) Vehicle standards relevant to the services provided under customer services agreements.

Please provide details of the health and safety audit and verification processes you have adopted for transport activities and WHS generally as relevant to the services provided under customer services agreements. As a minimum, we would expect that you have in place:

(i)            Processes to actively check (through inspection and/or auditing) that the SMS and accompanying procedures are being complied with by workers (including any subcontractors); 
(ii)           Governance activities including regular reporting to the business on key performance indicators (e.g. performance statistics, lag and lead indicators, incidents and breaches).
